description: Get dinner on the table in 25 minutes with this easy frittata recipe. It's packed with peas and feta, and is a great choice for brunch or a midweek dinner.
name: Pea, Feta & Rocket Frittata Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat grill to medium-high. Heat oil in a 22.5cm (base measurement, 5.5cm deep) ovenproof frying pan over medium heat. Cook zucchini for 4 minutes, stirring, or until softened. Add garlic and 1 1/2 cups peas and cook for 1 minute, stirring, or until peas are warmed through. Stir in half of the rocket.

Meanwhile, whisk eggs and milk in a large jug until combined. Season with pepper. Pour egg mixture over pea mixture in pan. Sprinkle over tasty and parmesan cheeses, then cook for 7 minutes, without stirring, or until frittata edge starts to set.
Scatter over feta and remaining peas. Place pan under grill and cook for 5 minutes or until frittata has set. Serve topped with remaining rocket.
